               <head>Savanih-i ahval-i Ashob</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Savāniḥ-i ʿumrī-yi Āshūb by Mīrzā Muḥammad Bakhsh Āshūb ibn Muḥammad Ghiyās̲</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85010050 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 " n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3938-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="person_f5798">Mīrzā Muḥammad Bakhsh Āshūb ibn Muḥammad Ghiyās̲</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f5798" type="alt">ميرزا محمّد بخش آشوب ابن محمّد غياث</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21960">Savāniḥ-i ʿumrī-yi Āshūb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21960">سوانح عمرى آشوب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternatively known by the title: <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Savāniḥ-i aḥvāl-i Āshūb</term>
                        </p>
                        <p>Alternative title on binding spine: Life of Ashub</p>
                        <p>Alternative title on binding label: Siwanih i 'Umri of Mhd Bakhsh (Ashob)</p>
                        <p>Brief <term xml:lang="en">autobiography</term>, generally lacking chronological details
                        </p>
                        <p>Supplementary account of the author's elder <term xml:lang="en">brother</term>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7725" role="subject">Muẓaffar Ḥusayn 'Ḥusayn'</persName>, including his poems
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>According to a note (f. 1r) by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">George Jasper Nicholls</persName>, this manuscript has been copied from a volume lent by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7745" role="oth">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Sattār</persName>, of <name type="place">Bhitrī (Ghāzīpūr)</name>
